java.lang.Object
  edu.mit.jwi.data.AbstractCachingDataSource

public abstract class AbstractCachingDataSource
extends java.lang.Object
implements IDictionaryDataSource

An abstract adapter on IDictionaryDataSource that adds the ability to cache lines.

Since:
1.5.0
Version:
1.00, 4/20/06
Author:
Mark A. Finlayson

setInitialCapacity

public void setInitialCapacity(int capacity)
Sets the initial capacity of the cache. If the cache has already been initialized, this method has no effect until the cache is released (releaseCache()) and re-initialized (initializeCache(int)).

initializeCache

protected void initializeCache(int capacity)
Creates (or resets) the cache. Subclasses don't need to call this directly; it is called via the setCachingEnabled(boolean) method.
